import {dep} from '../../../data/site';
---

<DocsLayout title="Funktor" sidebar={funktorSidebar} description="A modular Ktor-based server framework for Kotlin">

    <h1>Funktor</h1>

    <p class="text-xl text-gray-400 !mt-2 !mb-8">
        A modular server framework built on Ktor. Auth, REST APIs, clustering, messaging,
        and more &mdash; wired together with Kontainer.
    </p>

    <h2>Why Funktor?</h2>

    <p>Ktor gives you an HTTP server. It does not give you authentication, background jobs, file storage, distributed
        locks,
        email sending, request profiling, or a CLI framework. You wire all of that up yourself, every time.</p>

    <Aside>We built about five Ktor apps before extracting Funktor. Each one had its own auth middleware, its own retry
        logic,
        its own &ldquo;just throw it in a coroutine&rdquo; job runner. Funktor is what those five apps wished they had.
    </Aside>

    <p>Funktor is a set of modules that snap together. Use what you need, ignore the rest. Every module integrates with
        <a href="/ultra/kontainer/">Kontainer</a> for dependency injection, giving you per-request scoping across the
        entire
        stack.</p>

    <Code code={`funktorApp {
    server {
        funktorCore()
        funktorRest()
        funktorAuth {
            useKarango()
        }
        funktorCluster {
            useKarango()
        }
        funktorMessaging {
            useKarango()
        }
    }
}`} lang="kotlin" theme="vitesse-dark"/>

