    <h2>How it fits together</h2>

    <p>Every Funktor module registers its services in
        <a href="/ultra/kontainer/">Kontainer</a>. When a request arrives, Ktor creates a fresh container instance.
        Services
        that need the current user, request metrics, or audit context get them via constructor injection &mdash; no
        parameter
        threading, no thread-locals.</p>

    <p>Data persistence uses <a href="/ultra/karango/">Karango</a> (ArangoDB) or <a href="/ultra/monko/">Monko</a>
        (MongoDB).
        Both are pluggable per module &mdash; the auth module can use Karango while the logging module uses Monko, or
        vice versa.</p>

    <Aside>Funktor is opinionated about architecture but not about databases.
        Each module declares what it needs; you choose which backend provides it.
    </Aside>

